      "writtenOn": "2020-10-05T16:21:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "we have contention from multiple threads on s_works. is there a way to get rid of this contention?\n\nfor instance, since we calculate the balance of the work up front, we should already know which thread is going to run which work, which means we can keep a local vector of WorkItem* per thread (they could also be combined into a MessageChannel\u003cWorkItem, 1\u003e to allow the thread to block quietly once there\u0027s no work, using its own lock/cv instead of having a global one (see SyncThread.cpp for an example of using a MessageChannel)",
